ft=5|in=9.6}}\n| [[Bangalore]]\n| Top 10\n|}\n\n==Grand Finale Judges==\n* Anntonia Porsild - Miss Supranational 2019 from [[Thailand]]\n* [[Asha Bhat]] - Miss Supranational 2014 from [[India]]\n* [[Jacqueline Fernandez|Anil Kapoor]] - Bollywood Actor\n* [[Aditya Roy Kapur|Aditya Roy Kapoor]] - Bollywood Actor\n* [[Lara Dutta]] - [[Miss Universe 2000]]\n* Nikhil Mehra - Designer\n* Shivan Bhatiya - Fashion Designer\n*Narresh Kukreja - Fashion Designer\n* Gavin Miguel - Designer\n\n==Selection of participants==\nTwenty delegates would be selected to compete in the grand finale.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/amp/life-style/miss-diva-2020-is-back-for-all-the-talented-girls-to-make-their-grand-career-in-the-glamour-industry--582894|title=Miss Diva 2020 is back for all the talented girls to make their grand career in the Glamour Industry|work=The Hans India|date=20 November 2019}}</ref> Among them, thirteen participants were selected from various rounds of city audition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tkop.org/2019/12/26/miss-diva-2020-first-impressions-review-miss-universe-india/amp/|title=The batch of Miss Diva - Miss Universe India 2020|date=26 December 2019}}</ref> Five finalists were selected through ''Campus Princess 2019'' auditions.\nThe winner of ''Miss North-East Diva'', a regional contest conducted by the [[Miss Diva|Miss India Organization]], for aspirants from the [[Northeast India]] gets direct entry in the Top 20. This competition was won by Malashya Kashyap.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.northeastlivetv.com/2019/08/05/malashya-kashyap-wins-engage-north-east-diva-2019-crown/|title=Malashya Kashyap wins Engage North East Diva 2019 crown|date=2019-08-05|work=North East Live|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pragjyotishcollege.ac.in/malashya-kashyap-h-s-2nd-year-student-is-the-winner-of-north-east-diva-2019-top-20-finalist-of-miss-diva-universe-2020-of-times-group-of-india/|title=Malashya Kashyap, H.S. 2nd Year student is the winner of North East Diva 2019 & Top 20 finalist of Miss Diva Universe 2020|website=pragjyotishcollege.ac.in|access-date=2019-10-05}}</ref> One delegate got a [[Wild card (cards)|Wildcard]] entry, whose winner was decided on the basis of public vote.<ref>{{cite news|  url=https://thegreatpageantcommunity.com/2019/12/25/liva-miss-diva-2020-contestants/|work=| title=Liva Miss Diva 2020 Contestants!|date=25 December 2019}}</ref> Vaishnavi Ganesh won the Wild Card entry.\n\n===City Finalists===\nFollowing are the finalists selected in auditions conducted at various cities of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.auditionform.in/miss-diva-2019-auditions-registration/|title=Liva Miss Diva 2020 Auditions and Registration|website=|date=11 November 2019}}</ref> They would be further shortlisted and finalized as the contestants of Liva Miss Diva 2020 pageant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianage.com/amp/life/fashion/141119/miss-diva-2020-strong-dynamic-confident-is-back-with-new-season.html|title=Miss Diva is back with a new season.|work=The Asian Age|date=14 November 2019}}</ref> Few delegates selected by the [[Femina Miss India|Miss India Organization]] competed in the Wildcard round in [[Mumbai]]. The winner of this round would be selected with a combination of public voting & internal jury members.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.beautypageants.in/liva-miss-diva-2020-all-set-to-announce-wildcard-entry-contest/eventshow/72922521.cms|title=Liva Miss Diva 2020 all set to announce Wildcard entry|website=Indiatimes|access-date=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n;Color key\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|#FFBCD9|border=darkgray}} Shortlisted as Miss Diva 2020 contestant.\n* {{Color box|lightgreen|border=darkgray}} Advanced to Top 20 by winning the Wildcard public vote.\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#BEBEBE\"\n! [[Lucknow]]\n! [[Hyderabad]]\n! [[Chennai]]\n! [[Kolkata]]\n! [[Indore]]\n! [[Pune]]\n! [[Banglore]]\n! [[Jaipur]]\n! [[Chandigarh]]\n! [[Delhi]]\n! [[Mumbai]]\n|-\n| Anushka Kumar\n| Aishwarya S\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|[[Adline Castelino]]\n| Akshita Singh\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|[[Aavriti Choudhary]]\n| Mehek Vinayak\n| Anjali Anish\n| Ankita Trivedi\n| Devianna Ahluwalia\n| Akanksha Choudhary\n| Alankrita Shahi\n|-\n| Ishika Bisht\n| Bella Lolage\n| Aishwarya Dinesh\n| Meghna Bose\n| Alisha Khan\n| Naina Sharma\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Lavanya Gunasekar\n| Kanchan Khatana\n| Jasmine Singh\n| Arshiya Sharma\n| Aneesha Rane\n|-\n| Komal Khillare\n| Bhavna Sirpa\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Farhat Firoza\n| Megna Mukherjee\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Anisha Sharma\n| Natasha Das\n| Manmeet Kaur\n| Rubal Shekhawat\n| Shreya Suri\n| Devika Mahajan\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|[[Archana Ravi]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Rashalika Sabharwal\n| Harshita Sharma\n| Neha Jha\n| Rashmi Madhuri\n| Monika Dwivedi\n| Nimisha Chavan\n| Rashmitha R\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Rushali Yadav\n| Shyna\n| Elix Chaudhary\n| Naveli Deshmukh\n|-\n| Simran Singh\n| Madhushree Gupta\n| Prithivee\n| \u00d7\n| Ridhima Firke\n| Niyamat Nilgiriwala\n| R Vishnupriya\n| Samridhi Ahlawat\n| Simran Kapoor\n| Ilika Tyagi\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Payal Sharma\n|-\n| Sukraty Saxena\n| Sri Lakshmi\n| Rubeiya SK\n| \u00d7\n| Senhapriya Roy\n| Sachi Kudale\n| Simran Pareek\n| Simran Sharma\n| Ushtu Chiber\n| Lavanya John\n| Ritika Nayak\n|-\n| \u00d7\n| Sri Sai Reddy\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| Tanya Mittal\n| Sakshi Bhosale\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\"|Vaishnavi Ganesh\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| Lavanya Sangwan\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Roshini Sharma\n|-\n| \u00d7\n| Soundarya Gowda\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| Tejal Patil\n| Tanisha Pal\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| Ritika Nayak\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Shivangi Sharma\n|-\n| \u00d7\n| Taruna Choudhary\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| Vaibhavi Sharma\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| Shreya Bahukhandi\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Sruthi Periyasamy\n|-\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| \u00d7\n| style=\"background:#FFBCD9;\"|Tanya Subramanian\n| \u00d7\n|}\n\n===Campus Princess===\nThe winner of [[Femina Miss India|Campus Princess 2019]] gets direct entry to the contest. In addition, four other finalists from the auditions were finalized as [[Miss Diva|Liva Miss Diva]] contestants. The following contestants will compete in the Liva Miss Diva 2020 pageant.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:50%;\" | Delegates\n! style=\"width:25%;\" | Notes\n|-\n| Shreya Poonja\n| Winner\n|-\n| Nishi Bharadwaj\n| rowspan=4| Selected finalists\n|-\n| Neha Jaiswal\n|-\n| Megha Sachdeva\n|-\n| Arshina Sumbul\n|}\n\n==Crossovers & Returnees==\nContestants who previously competed in previous editions of [[Miss Diva|Liva Miss Diva]] and other local and international beauty pageants with their respective placements.\n\n==== National Pageants ====\n;[[Femina Miss India|Femina Miss India 2019]]\n* Chhattisgarh: Anisha Sharma ('''Top 3''')\n* Chhattisgarh: Farhat Firoza ('''Top 3''')\n* Kerala: [[Archana Ravi]] ('''Top 3''')\n* Tamil Nadu: Suruthi Periyasamy ('''Top 3''')\n* Uttarakhand: Shivangi Sharma ('''Top 3''')\n\n;[[Glamanand Supermodel India]]\n* [[Glamanand Supermodel India 2018|2018]]: Nishi Bhardawaj ('''Miss Earth India''')\n\n;[[India's Next Top Model]]\n* [[India's Next Top Model (season 4)|2018]]: Rushali Yadav ('''2nd Runner-up''')\n\n;Elite Miss Rajasthan\n* 2016: Neha Jaiswal ('''Winner''')\n* 2018: Arshina Sumbul ('''Winner''')\n\n==== International Pageants ====\n;[[Miss Earth]]\n* [[Miss Earth 2018|2018]]: Nishi Bhardawaj\n\n;Miss Super Globe\n* 2018: [[Archana Ravi]] ('''1st Runner-up''')\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n{{Miss Diva}}\n\n[[Category:2020 beauty pageants]]\n[[Category:2019 in India]]\n[[Category:Miss Diva]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Beauty pageant edition}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox beauty pageant\n| image          = File:Miss Diva 2020 logo.jpg\n| represented    =\n| photo          =\n| caption        =\n| photogenic     = Roshni Sharma\n| congeniality   = Nishi Bharadwaj\n| best national costume = Malashya Kashyap\n| date           = 22 February 2020\n| presenters     = [[Malaika Arora Khan]]<br> Sachin Kumbhar\n| acts           = [[Jacqueline Fernandez]]<br>[[Ishaan Khattar]]<br> Hari & Sukhmani\n| venue          = Yash Raj Studio, Andheri West, Mumbai\n| broadcaster    = [[MTV (Indian TV channel)|MTV India]]\n| entrants       = 20\n| placements     = 10\n| winner         = '''[[Adline Castelino]]'''\n| before         = [[Miss Universe India 2019|2019]]\n| next           = 2021\n}}\n\n'''Miss Diva 2020''' was the 8th edition of [[Miss Diva]] contest held on 22 February 2020. A total of twenty contestants were shortlisted from various auditions across the country. [[Miss Universe India 2019]], [[Vartika Singh]] crowned [[Adline Castelino]] as her successor. She will represent [[India]] at [[Miss Universe 2020]]. Miss Supranational India 2019, ''Shefali Sood'' crowned ''[[Aavriti Choudhary]]'' as her successor and she will represent India at Miss Supranational 2020. [[Miss Diva 2018]] Runner up ''Roshni Sheoran'' crowned ''Neha Jaiswal'' as her successor. Anntonia Porsild, [[:pl:Miss Supranational 2019|Miss Supranational 2019]] graced the event. This was the first edition of Miss Diva under ''Liva Fluid Fashion''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livafluidfashion.com/|title=LIVA Fluid Fashion {{!}} Birla Cellulose {{!}} Clothing by Aditya Birla Group - LIVA|website=www.livafluidfashion.com|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://beautypageants.indiatimes.com/missdivaform.cms?from=mdr|title=Miss Diva: Beauty Pageant Entry Form {{!}} Apply Online for Miss Diva Beauty Contest|website=beautypageants.indiatimes.com|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n\n==Final results==\n;Color keys\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|#50C878|border=darkgray}} Declared as the winner in an International pageant.\n* {{Color box|#89CFF0|border=darkgray}} Ended as Runner-up in an International pageant.\n* {{Color box|#F2CECE|border=darkgray}} Ended as finalist or semifinalist in an International pageant.\n* {{Color box|#FFFACD|border=darkgray}} Unplaced.\n}}\n{| class=\"sortable\" border=\"5\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #FFFFFF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#787878\" colspan=10 hialign=\"center\"\n|align=\"center\" width=\"280\"|<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">'''Final Results'''</span>||align=\"center\" width=\"250\"|<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">'''Candidate'''</span>|| align=\"center\" width=\"300\"|<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">'''International Placement'''</span>\n|-\n! Miss Universe India 2020\n|\n* '''[[Adline Castelino]]'''\n| ''TBD''\n|-\n! Miss Diva - Supranational 2020\n|\n* '''[[Aavriti Choudhary]]'''\n| ''TBD''\n|-\n! Miss Diva Runner-up\n|\n* '''Neha Jaiswal'''\n|-\n! Top 5\n|\n* Anisha Sharma\n* Roshni Sharma\n|-\n! Top 10\n|\n* [[Archana Ravi]]\n* Arshina Sumbul\n* Malashya Kashyap\n* Rushali Yadav\n* Vaishnavi Ganesh\n|}\n\n=== Special Awards ===\n{| class=\"sortable\" border=\"5\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #FFFFFF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#787878\" colspan=10 hialign=\"center\"\n| align=\"center\" width=\"280\"|<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">'''Award'''</span>||align=\"center\" width=\"250\"|<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF\">'''Winner'''</span>\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Grand Finale\n|-\n| '''Miss Multimedia'''\n| [[Archana Ravi]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Preliminary shows\n|-\n| '''Best National Costume'''\n| Malashya Kashyap\n|-\n| '''Miss Body Beautiful'''\n| Malashya Kashyap\n|-\n| '''Miss Congeniality'''\n| Nishi Bharadwaj\n|-\n| '''Miss Glowing Skin'''\n| Rashalika Sabharwal\n|-\n| '''Miss Lifestyle'''\n| Nishi Bharadwaj\n|-\n| '''Miss Photogenic'''\n| Roshni Sharma\n|-\n| '''Miss Radio Jockey'''\n| Anisha Sharma\n|-\n| '''Miss Shinning Star'''\n| Rashalika Sabharwal\n|-\n| '''Miss Sudoku'''\n| Rushali Yadav\n|-\n| '''Miss Talented'''\n| Lavanya Gunasekar<br>Malashya Kashyap\n|-\n| '''Miss Top Model'''\n| Rushali Yadav\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Bennett University Sports day\n|-\n| '''Miss Smasher - Badminton'''\n| Adline Castelino\n|-\n|'''Miss Iron Maiden'''\n| Lavanya Gunasekar\n|-\n|'''Miss Active'''\n| Farhat Firoza\n|-\n| '''Miss Hopper - Basketball'''\n| Roshni Sharma\n|-\n| '''Miss Pool Shark'''\n| rowspan=2|Shivangi Sharma\n|-\n| '''Table Tennis'''\n|}\n\n==Background==\nIn 2019, <u>Liva Fluid Fashion</u><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livafluidfashion.com/|title=LIVA Fluid Fashion {{!}} Birla Cellulose {{!}} Clothing by Aditya Birla Group - LIVA|website=www.livafluidfashion.com|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref> acquired [[Miss Diva]] franchise. On 11 November 2019, the organization announced in a press conference that the pageant will be held in February 2020.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.face2news.com/news/59365-liva-miss-diva-miss-universe-india-2020-gets-tremendous-response.aspx|work=| title=Miss Diva - Miss Universe India 2020 gets tremendous response\n|date=14 December 2019}}</ref> Contestants will be selected through auditions in various cities across the country. Those shortlisted contestants will go through final round of auditions in [[Mumbai]] to get top finalists who will compete at pageant. [[Miss Universe 2000]], [[Lara Dutta]] will serve as the mentor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.femina.in/celebs/indian/liva-miss-diva-2020-strong-dynamic-and-confident-is-back-142648.amp|title=Liva Miss Diva 2020- Strong, Dynamic and Confident is back|work=Femina|date=10 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Format===\nA new format was introduced by the Organization this year. Top 10 candidates would be selected based on their performance in the [[preliminary]] segment and closed door interview. The Top 10 delegates will have an opportunity to speak about themselves in an opening statement. They would furthur compete in swimsuit and evening gown rounds to determine the Final 5. A common question would be asked to all the Top 5 delegates. They would be finalized into Top 3.\n\n==Contestants==\nThe following are the 20 contestants participating in the Liva Miss Diva 2020:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tkop.org/2019/12/22/miss-universe-india-2020-meet-the-finalists-of-miss-diva-2020/|title=Miss Universe India 2020: Meet The Finalists of Miss Diva 2020!|website=tkop.org}}</ref>\n;Color key\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|gold|border=darkgray}} Declared as Winner\n* {{Color box|#FFF83B|border=darkgray}} Ended as Runner-up\n* {{Color box|#FFFACD|border=darkgray}} Ended as one of the Finalists or Semi-finalists\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; line-height:20px; width:800px; margin:auto;\" <!--- Please do not change the width this allows the table to scale within page margins based on display. --->\n!scope=\"col\";| Nu.\n!scope=\"col\" | Contestant\n!scope=\"col\" | Age{{efn|Ages at the time of the pageant}}\n!scope=\"col\" | Height\n!scope=\"col\" | Hometown\n!scope=\"col\" | Placement\n|-\n|style=\"background-color:#FFF83B\"| 1\n|style=\"background-color:#FFF83B\"| [[Aavriti Choudhary]]\n|style=\"background-color:#FFF83B\"| 21\n|style=\"background-color:#FFF83B\"| {{Height|ft=5|in=7}}\n|style=\"background-color:#FFF83B\"| [[Jabalpur]]\n|style=\"background-color:#FFF83B\"| Miss Diva Supranational 2020\n|-\n|style=\"background-color:gold\"| '''2'''\n|style=\"background-color:gold\"| '''[[Adline Castelino]]'''\n|style=\"background-color:gold\"| '''21'''\n|style=\"background-color:gold\"| '''{{Height|ft=5|in=6.4}}'''\n|style=\"background-color:gold\"| '''[[Udupi]]''